    • Method Detail

      • abortAccept

        public static int abortAccept​(long fd)
        Aborts blocking accept() call. On Darwin and Windows this method simply closes the underlying file descriptor. On Linux this method calls shutdown().

        Once accept() exists it is by convention liable for closing its own file descriptor.

        Parameters:
        fd - file descriptor
        Returns:
        0 when call was successful and -1 otherwise. In case of error errno() would return error code.

      • isDead

        public static boolean isDead​(long fd)
        This method reads 1 byte (or none if the socket is non blocking and there is no data). If there is no error (EOF ?) then it returns false If there is an error (EOF ?) then it returns true
        Parameters:
        fd - network file descriptor
        Returns:
        check the description
